en sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add prawns, pineapple, 5 g curry powder, rice wine, fish sauce and salt then, without measuring cup, stir-fry <b>7 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Transfer to a serving dish then add reserved cooked rice, peas, carrots and eggs (see tip). Mix well and serve hot."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If desired, frozen peas and carrots can be added to cook in the sauce in <b>step 6<b> instead of steamed in <b>step 2.<b>","Tiger prawns are large prawns with stripey markings. If tiger prawns are not available, substitute with any raw prawns.","If there is a black line down the back of the prawn, it means that the vein is full. It’s not harmful to eat, but the prawn looks better without it, and it can be gritty to eat. To devein prawns, lift the vein out using the tip of a small sharp knife or a cocktail stick.","For more attractive presentation, in <b>step 6,<b> roll up steamed eggs using baking paper and slice thinly. Arrange seafood and sliced eggs on rice."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","2 portions"]}